      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12383#M12383</link>
      <description>Cultural embroidery needles followed by the cultural sewing kits is not a bad way.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Switching to the fine steel plate gets a bit expensive, but you can recoop a lot of the cost &lt;i&gt;if&lt;/i&gt; your combines are successful. To keep the cost down, you need to make sure the trivial is just a hair above your current skill. Also, make sure you have the &lt;a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=7354" target="_blank"&gt;geerlok automated hammer&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Edit: You may also want to start investing in a &amp;quot;tradeskill suit&amp;quot; that maximizes INT or WIS. You can also ask for buffs in PoK. You can do a STR &amp;quot;suit&amp;quot; for smithing, but several of the worthwhile (self use and sell for profit) items require subcombines in the other tradeskills (brewing, jewelcraft, pottery,..), thus an INT or WIS suit is best in the long run.&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by ether_sphynx on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;04-04-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;01:03 PM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
