      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a general tip, the guides that are linked on the main page of eq traders are sometimes out of date.  I would try the complete tradeskill guide which is on their message boards, here instead:  &lt;a target="_blank" href="http://mboards.eqtraders.com/eq/showthread.php?t=25961"&gt;http://mboards.eqtraders.com/eq/showthread.php?t=25961&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Sewing kits are definitely the way to go until 162.  You can do enchanted velium bits moderately cheaply if you farm the velium yourself (kill tizmaks in GD and convert the velium weapons), and then Shadowscream can take you up farther.  I avoided shadowscream for a long time, but it's actually not as bad as it looks, and it's pretty cheap.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
